node.text:
⁣So far I've only been ordering food in on the weekend, it gives me something to look forward to and some semblance of time and what day of the week it is⠀
⠀
Yesterday was the biggest treat thus far- a takeaway pithivier from Odette, filled with pigeon, foie, and bresse chicken. It's served alongside truffled pomme puree, sauce Perigueux(Demi glacé with truffle and Madeira), and a Kombu salad. ⠀
⠀
Odette is currently running a #odetteathome plating competition with some really amazing top 3 prizes. It's actually a lot of fun... because let's be real, plating is the most fun when you don't have to do any of the mise en place 🙄, also, when else will you get to see 3 Michelin starred food on your decades old Corelle dinnerware
@pengloh riiight? Not even going to try 😂
Damn....how to dare enter when you already sewn this up...
Duuuddeeee. I love canales!!! They look perfect. All the dishes do. Respect
Did u heat up ur knife?
are u gonna work in odette?🤣
I’m seeing u on channel u now and I came here to kaypoh LOL
Corelle dinnerware is the way to go @hanhaojuan
That plate on number 3 is legendary 😁
Looks nicer on the Corelle than Bernadaud 😉
Look at those beautiful air cells in the last pic. ❤️
@therealk1ngk0ng Dude I’m still trying to undo the damage done the entire of winter last year
@gabssee same gained weight while you were here HAHAHAHAH
@gabssee hey remember when we ate something like this at grapes and soda
so pretty. Inspiring me to do better. Thank you. Have a good fine day and take care.
